  "text": "Oligodendrocytes are susceptible to viral infection and have not been reported to have particularly heavy involvement during CNS infection with other pathogens. Oligodendrocytes have, however, been shown to secrete complement proteins when stimulated with Aspergillus fumigatus, a common fungal pathogen in immunosuppressed humans [CITATION_1] . Whether similar reactions occur during CM, and if C. neoformans infects oligodendrocytes, is not known.",
